Hi Shane.  The 12-469 comes with clicking.  Many people actually get so used
to it that they end up preferring it.  There are other radios that have been
hacked.. 12-820 Radio Shack armband which I believe is being discontinued,
the RS 20-125, and I believe a Sangean..  Go to my friend Steve Hultay&#39;s
website www.keyportparanormal.com &lt;http://www.keyportparanormal.com/&gt;  for a
complete list and instructions on how to hack these different models.  He
also has some You Tube videos of each radio scanning.



You can step up and purchase a Minibox which offers an adjustable sweep rate
from Paranormal Systems.  They are on the expensive side but they are
awesome boxes and Rick offers lay-away plans.  There is also a FM box by Joe
Cioppi that I personally love called of course Joe&#39;s Box.  Like Frank Joe
makes them by himself so these aren&#39;t out there to purchase like a
storefront. Don&#39;t forget that an older Knob style radio works great for a
manual sweep which many swear by it.  You probably already have a knob dial
radio in your house right now!  Just sweep up and down the dial at a pace
that just hits each station.  Don&#39;t linger but don&#39;t go so fast that no
sound is heard.  Frank makes wonderful boxes - the original &quot;Franks Box&quot; -
but he does not sell them.  



As for hosting audio I use www.ESNIPS.com &lt;http://www.esnips.com/&gt;  .  It
allows 5GB of free space to upload your files. 



I hope this helps.

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Not given
Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 9:45 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Hi and a couple of questions








First off my name is Shane. I just recently (past few weeks) heard about
ghost boxes. 

I watched a few videos and read some stuff on building several different
types (modifying existing devices).

I started with the 12-469 the completely white one. My first go around not
much happened but the second go around I got the same name twice and a hello
and a response of good after I asked how they were doing. 

I haven&#39;t had much time to really dig into it good, but one thing is
glaringly obvious is the annoying and constant ticking sound it makes is
there anyway to disable this or should I just move to a different radio?

I chose this one because of the cost and 2 because of the various footage I
saw and their results. I just didn&#39;t notice the horrific ticking as it
scanned through the AM band. ( I haven&#39;t had any luck with FM and haven&#39;t
tried much since it seems to find so many stations and doesn&#39;t sweep through
fast enough kinda invalidating anything I might have caught.)

Second is there a sight you recommend for hosting files that a good
contingent of people see as reputable?

Thanks in advance.

Shane




